QuakeCode – Privacy Policy

Last Updated: June 24, 2025

This privacy policy describes how QuakeCode (referred to as “the app”) collects, uses, and protects user data. QuakeCode is a mobile application focused on AI-powered earthquake prediction.

1. Data Collected

QuakeCode may collect the following types of data:
	•	Device Information: Operating system version, device model, and other basic system details
	•	Location Data: Used only when the user explicitly grants permission, for location-based earthquake analysis
	•	App Usage Data: Frequency and manner of app usage
	•	User Feedback and Reports: Voluntary input about felt earthquakes

2. Purpose of Data Collection

Collected data is used for the following purposes:
	•	To improve earthquake prediction algorithms
	•	To deliver location-based alerts and insights
	•	To enhance user experience
	•	To troubleshoot technical issues

3. Data Sharing with Third Parties

QuakeCode does not share personal data with third parties. However, anonymized and aggregated data may be used for academic research or AI model deployment.

4. Data Storage and Deletion

Data is stored securely. When the user deletes the app, all local data is removed from the device. Users may also request complete deletion of any stored data on our servers.

5. User Rights

Users have the right to:
	•	Understand what data is collected and how it is used
	•	Request deletion of their data
	•	Deny or revoke location access at any time

6. Contact

If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy policy, please contact us at:
